        <p class="text-xl text-zinc-600 max-w-2xl leading-relaxed">
          Premium walk-in closet systems built from furniture-grade plywood and solid hardwoods — no particle board, no wire shelving, no compromises.
        </p>
      </header>

      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-16 mb-24">
        <div class="lg:col-span-8 space-y-8 text-lg text-zinc-600 leading-relaxed">

          <section class="reveal" id="what-is-custom-closet-built-ins">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">What Are Custom Closet Built-Ins?</h2>
            <p class="speakable-intro">
              Custom closet built-ins are permanent, precision-fitted storage systems designed and built to the exact dimensions of your closet space. Unlike wire shelving from Home Depot or modular kits from The Container Store, custom built-ins are anchored to studs, use furniture-grade materials, and become a permanent improvement that increases your home's appraisal value.
            </p>
            <p>
              At <a href="/" class="text-yellow-600 font-bold hover:underline">First Class WoodWorks</a>, we build every closet system in our Murrieta shop using the same dovetail joinery and Blum soft-close hardware found in our <a href="/services/custom-kitchen-cabinets" class="text-yellow-600 font-bold hover:underline">custom kitchen cabinets</a>. Each piece is sealed with post-catalyzed conversion varnish for decades of performance in Southern California's heat and humidity cycles.
            </p>
          </section>

          <div class="relative rounded-sm overflow-hidden shadow-2xl reveal">
            <Image src={builtinImage} alt="Custom closet built-in system with dovetail drawers installed by First Class WoodWorks in Murrieta CA" width={800} height={600} class="w-full h-auto object-cover" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
          </div>

          <section class="reveal">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">Why Murrieta Homeowners Choose Custom Over Wire Shelving</h2>
            <p>
              Standard wire shelving flexes under weight, pulls away from drywall within 3-5 years, and wastes 30-40% of usable vertical space. Our custom built-ins use every square inch of your closet, from floor to ceiling, with adjustable shelving, pull-out drawers, shoe cubbies, valet rods, and felt-lined jewelry compartments.
            </p>
            <p>
              The difference shows at resale. Riverside County assessors classify custom built-ins as permanent improvements that add to property value — wire shelving and freestanding organizers are classified as personal property that leaves with the seller. Homes in Murrieta's Bear Creek, Greer Ranch, and Copper Canyon neighborhoods with professional closet systems sell 15-20 days faster than comparable properties with builder-grade closets.
            </p>
          </section>

          <section class="reveal bg-zinc-50 p-8 rounded-sm border border-zinc-100">
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-6 text-center">Custom Built-Ins vs. Alternatives</h3>
            <div class="overflow-x-auto">
              <table class="w-full text-sm text-left">
                <thead class="border-b border-zinc-200">
                  <tr>
                    <th class="pb-4 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider">Feature</th>
                    <th class="pb-4 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-zinc-400">Wire / Modular Kits</th>
                    <th class="pb-4 font-bold uppercase tracking-wider text-yellow-600">First Class Custom</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-zinc-200">
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Materials</td><td class="py-4">Coated wire or melamine</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Furniture-grade plywood & hardwoods</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Fit</td><td class="py-4">Standard sizes with gaps</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Built to 1/16th-inch precision</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Hardware</td><td class="py-4">Plastic brackets, basic rods</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Blum soft-close (lifetime warranty)</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Joinery</td><td class="py-4">Friction-fit or screws</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Dovetail drawer boxes</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Lifespan</td><td class="py-4">3-5 years before sagging</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">Lifetime (heirloom quality)</td></tr>
                  <tr><td class="py-4 font-bold">Home Value</td><td class="py-4">No appraisal impact</td><td class="py-4 font-bold text-zinc-900">5-10% value increase</td></tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>

          <section class="reveal">
            <h2 class="text-3xl font-serif font-bold text-zinc-900 mb-4">What Goes Into a First Class Closet System</h2>
            <p>
              Every closet project starts with an in-home consultation where we take laser measurements and discuss how you actually use your closet — not how a catalog thinks you should. We then produce full 3D renderings so you approve the design before we cut the first board.
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-3 my-6">
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span> <span><strong>Double-hang sections</strong> — two rods at 40" and 80" for shirts, pants, and jackets</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span> <span><strong>Full-height sections</strong> — for dresses, coats, and long garments</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span> <span><strong>Dovetail drawer banks</strong> — Blum soft-close undermount slides for folded items</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span> <span><strong>Slant-front shoe shelves</strong> — display instead of stack, visible at a glance</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span> <span><strong>Pull-out valet rods</strong> — outfit planning and next-day staging</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span> <span><strong>Integrated LED lighting</strong> — Hafele Loox strips concealed in crown molding</span></li>
              <li class="flex items-start gap-3"><span class="text-yellow-600 font-bold mt-1">&#10003;</span> <span><strong>Felt-lined jewelry drawers</strong> — Blum soft-close with divided compartments</span></li>
            </ul>
          </section>

          <div class="relative rounded-sm overflow-hidden shadow-2xl reveal">
            <Image src={builtinImage2} alt="Walk-in closet built-in with adjustable shelving and LED lighting by First Class WoodWorks Murrieta" width={800} height={600} class="w-full h-auto object-cover" loading="lazy" decoding="async" />
